While temporal retrieval can enhance relevance for time-specific queries, it may yield zero tuples when the news coverage is sparse for query dates. In contrast, generic retrieval consistently provides tuples by first retrieving temporally relevant tuples and, if necessary, uses a back-off approach to additionally retrieve semantically relevant tuples.